{
  "info": {
    "name": "Guacamaya Net — Backend",
    "description": "Endpoint tests for the @guacamaya/backend Fastify HTTP server.\n\nSet the `baseUrl` collection variable (default `http://localhost:3000`).\n\nTwo feature domains:\n- **channels** — emergency broadcast channels (alertas, refugios, etc.)\n- **locations** — GPS trajectory history for the moving-map dashboard\n\n**Data-mule ingest is binary + zero-trust.** `POST /ingest` takes `{ \"frames\": [\"<base64>\"] }` — each frame is a signed 118 B Guacamaya mesh frame (22 B payload + 32 B pubkey + 64 B signature; a 119 B frame with the leading hop-TTL byte is also tolerated). Every frame is re-verified server-side (CRC16 → pubkey↔node_id binding → Ed25519) before anything is persisted; the backend never trusts the client. Verified frames become `verified:false` community records on `solicito-ayuda`, and the lat/lon inside the signed payload is persisted as a `LocationPoint` on the SAME path. **There is no trusted-JSON location ingest** — `GET /locations` is read-only.\n\nThe `validFrame` / `validFrame2` collection variables hold real signed frames (deterministic dev key) so the ingest request passes verification out of the box. Regenerate them with the script in `backend/scripts/gen-postman-frames.ts` if the wire format changes.\n\nIDs are recomputed server-side (SHA-256 of canonical content), so client-supplied `id` values are ignored for dedup purposes.\n\nNote: the WebSocket endpoint (`/ws`) is not testable from a standard Postman REST request; use Postman's WebSocket request type and connect to `ws://localhost:3000/ws`, then send `{\"type\":\"subscribe\",\"channel\":\"solicito-ayuda\"}` (or `\"locations\"` for the moving map).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "channelId",
      "value": "alertas",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "deviceId",
      "value": "device-9af220d724884841c19ba0285cf30c272b480e78c75977893daedec2184cb1f2",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Origin device of the sample frames (= device-<origin pubkey>). Used by the GET /locations filter."
    },
    {
      "key": "validFrame",
      "value": "CLkbyMoNvjhmfXzgzhRfxAIAEJKmEpryINckiEhBwZugKFzzDCcrSA54x1l3iT2u3sIYTLHyn2HsQ2oy60F1dkEPOc6sG3rkEKB+VkIWB/U8pHrhvqM1aL3YIm3KJWlWPshPV7YhQHLiUkmcZMUUMuyiLUSrCA==",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "A real signed 118 B mesh frame (medical SOS, critical, Guatemala City). Passes CRC + pubkey binding + Ed25519."
    },
    {
      "key": "validFrame2",
      "value": "CLlGwMoNj1hmfX84zhRfxBADEJMaYZryINckiEhBwZugKFzzDCcrSA54x1l3iT2u3sIYTLHyT/SPSe6pMwdxnPgl1YIg6ZDAUYMxFCgppgEeK92srUvlX30aLurHpI6bFsdrhd6bHdTvUhT8AfP3rhod3mnyDQ==",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "A second signed frame (water request) — different payload, different content-hash id."
    },
    {
      "key": "tamperedFrame",
      "value": "AAkbyMoNvjhmfXzgzhRfxAIAEJKmEpryINckiEhBwZugKFzzDCcrSA54x1l3iT2u3sIYTLHyn2HsQ2oy60F1dkEPOc6sG3rkEKB+VkIWB/U8pHrhvqM1aL3YIm3KJWlWPshPV7YhQHLiUkmcZMUUMuyiLUSrCA==",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "validFrame with a flipped payload byte — fails verification (rejected, not persisted)."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Meta",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET / — root",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": [""]
            },
            "description": "Welcome message. Confirms the server is reachable."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('has welcome message', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('message'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /health — health check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Liveness probe. Returns { ok: true }."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('ok is true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.eql(true));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /pubkey — backend public key",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/pubkey",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["pubkey"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the backend's Ed25519 public identity key (hex) used by clients to verify signed official records."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('returns publicKey', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('publicKey'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Channels",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /channels — list channels",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/channels",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["channels"]
            },
            "description": "Lists the available emergency channels and whether each accepts only verified (official) records."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('returns a non-empty array', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.be.an('array').that.is.not.empty;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /channels/:id/records — create official record",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"title\": \"Evacuación inmediata\",\n    \"body\": \"Diríjase al refugio más cercano por la ruta norte.\",\n    \"severity\": \"high\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/channels/{{channelId}}/records",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["channels", "{{channelId}}", "records"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a backend-signed (verified) record on the given channel, persists it, and broadcasts it to live WebSocket subscribers. The server sets timestamp, ttl, author, signature and the content-hash id."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const rec = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('record has id and signature', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(rec).to.have.property('id');",
                  "  pm.expect(rec).to.have.property('sig');",
                  "  pm.expect(rec.verified).to.eql(true);",
                  "});",
                  "if (rec && rec.timestamp) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('lastRecordTimestamp', rec.timestamp);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /channels/:id/records — missing payload (400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/channels/{{channelId}}/records",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["channels", "{{channelId}}", "records"]
            },
            "description": "Validation case: a request body without a `payload` field is rejected with 400."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 400', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                  "pm.test('has error message', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('error'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /channels/:id/records — list records since",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/channels/{{channelId}}/records?since=0",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["channels", "{{channelId}}", "records"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "since",
                  "value": "0",
                  "description": "unix ms; return only records with timestamp > since (default 0 = all)"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Retrieves records for a channel created after the `since` timestamp."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('returns an array', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /ingest — data-mule signed frame upload",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"frames\": [\n    \"{{validFrame}}\",\n    \"{{validFrame2}}\"\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/ingest",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["ingest"]
            },
            "description": "Uploads a batch of signed binary mesh frames (Base64) collected by a data mule. ZERO TRUST: each frame is re-decoded and its Ed25519 signature re-verified server-side (CRC16 → pubkey↔node_id binding → Ed25519) before anything is persisted. Verified frames become `verified:false` community records on `solicito-ayuda` (id = SHA-256 of the signed payload), and the lat/lon inside each payload is persisted as a LocationPoint on the same path. Response: `{ success, ingested, duplicate, rejected, locationsIngested, reasons }`.\n\nThe two sample frames pass verification. Run this once for `ingested:2`; run it again and the same frames dedup to `duplicate:2, ingested:0`."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const b = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('success with full ingest report', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.success).to.eql(true);",
                  "  pm.expect(b).to.have.property('ingested');",
                  "  pm.expect(b).to.have.property('duplicate');",
                  "  pm.expect(b).to.have.property('rejected');",
                  "  pm.expect(b).to.have.property('locationsIngested');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('valid frames are not rejected', () => pm.expect(b.rejected).to.eql(0));",
                  "pm.test('each ingested record also yields a location', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.locationsIngested).to.eql(b.ingested);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /ingest — tampered frame is rejected",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"frames\": [\n    \"{{tamperedFrame}}\"\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/ingest",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["ingest"]
            },
            "description": "Zero-trust gate: a frame with a flipped payload byte fails verification and is counted under `rejected` with a `reasons` breakdown — nothing is persisted. Demonstrates the backend never takes the client's word for authenticity."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const b = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('nothing ingested', () => pm.expect(b.ingested).to.eql(0));",
                  "pm.test('frame rejected with a reason', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.rejected).to.eql(1);",
                  "  pm.expect(Object.keys(b.reasons)).to.have.length.above(0);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /ingest — invalid frames array (400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"frames\": \"not-an-array\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/ingest",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["ingest"]
            },
            "description": "Validation case: `frames` missing or not an array returns 400."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 400', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                  "pm.test('has error message', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('error'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Locations",
      "description": "Location history is read-only at the HTTP edge. Points are NOT ingested here — they are derived from Ed25519-verified mesh frames in `POST /ingest` (see the Channels folder). The old `POST /ingest/locations` trusted-JSON endpoint was removed; the same crypto gate that guards records guards positions, and `deviceId` always comes from the verified origin pubkey.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /locations — moving-map query",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/locations?since=0&deviceId={{deviceId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["locations"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "since",
                  "value": "0",
                  "description": "unix ms; return only points with timestamp > since (default 0 = all)"
                },
                {
                  "key": "deviceId",
                  "value": "{{deviceId}}",
                  "description": "optional; filter to a single device's trajectory (= device-<origin pubkey>). Remove to get all devices. Run the /ingest frame upload first to populate data.",
                  "disabled": false
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns location points for the moving-map dashboard, optionally filtered by `since` and `deviceId`. Read-only — positions are populated by POST /ingest from verified frames."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('returns an array', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.be.an('array'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
